    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Simplified versions of carbon prints. These use silver bromide paper to make a contact print. These prints were then placed against pigment paper and through a chemical developer and warm water, and a pigmented print was created on the bleached original carrier. A double transfer, used for carbon printing, was no longer necessary.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
